  "doc_id": "35434",
  "text": "The formalin-fixed embedded histopathological tissue sections were mounted on glass slides and evaluated by fluorescence in situ hybridization (FISH) as previously described [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In brief, paraffin-embedded tissue specimens were deparaffinized using an automated system by passage through xylene (3 x 10 min), 100% alcohol (2 x 5 min), 95% ethanol (5 min), and finally 70% ethanol (5 min). The slides were next rapidly transported in deionized water to the DNA testing laboratory where they were air dried prior to hybridization. FISH probes 5'-labeled with either Cy-3 or FITC (Life Sciences) were reconstituted with DNAse-free water and diluted to a working concentration of 5 ng/μL (Table 1) .",
